cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the use of Agent Communication Languages (ACLs) within Multi Agent Systems (MAS), which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on reasoning about complex interaction protocols to facilitate conversations between agents, which is a key aspect of Multi Agent Systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of general-purpose agent programming languages in supporting complex reasoning about agent messaging, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of a prototype implementation within the Agent Factory multi agent framework, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of logical reasoning capabilities in agent programming languages, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
